			     Amiga Models and Specs V1.1


These are the main specifications of all Amiga computers sold from the A1000
to the A4000 Tower.  I haven't included special models because most of them are only
upgrades of standard models.



			
			 @{" Amiga 1000         " link A1000}
			 @{" Amiga  500         " link A500}
			 @{" Amiga 2000         " link A2000}
			 @{" Amiga 3000 Desktop " link A3000}
			 @{" Amiga 3000 Tower   " link A3000T}
			 @{" CDTV interactive   " link CDTV}
			 @{" Amiga  600         " link A600}
			 @{" Amiga 1200         " link A1200}
			 @{" Amiga 4000 Desktop " link A4000}
			 @{" Amiga 4000 Tower   " link A4000T}
			 @{" CD32 game console  " link CD32}



I will try to update as often as possible, if you have any specs to add or wrong
information that you notice or good ones that need to be included, please e-mail me
at this address: @{b}delta@teccart.qc.ca@{ub}



						    Mario Laflamme (1997)
@Endnode

@Node A1000 "Amiga 1000"
			      @{b}Amiga 1000@{ub}

Release Date:            1985
	 CPU:            68000 at 7.14 Mhz
	 FPU:            None
Custom Chips:            Denise - 8632 non half-bright
			 Paula
			 Agnus
       Video:            OCS (4096 colors)
  Kickstarts:            1.0, 1.1, 1.2 then 1.3 (all on floppy)
	RAM :            256K Chip on board
      Drives:            Internal 880K floppy
       SLOTS:            1 - RAM expansion
			 1 - Zorro
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 Parallel (male)
			 Serial (female)
			 15Khz RGB video
			 External Floppy
			 RJ12 Keyboard connector
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks
			 Color composite video output

POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - Up to 512K CHIP RAM
			 - Up to 8M FAST RAM
			 - Hard drive
			 - ...

@Endnode


@Node A500 "Amiga 500"
			      @{b}Amiga 500@{ub}

Release Date:            1987-1988
	 CPU:            68000 at 7.14 Mhz
	 FPU:            None
Custom Chips:            Denise - 8362 Denise, REV6.3+ had 8373 SuperDenise
			 Paula
			 Fat Agnus
			 Gary
       Video:            OCS or ECS (4096 colors)
  Kickstarts:            1.2 then 1.3
	RAM :            512K Chip on board
      Drives:            Internal 880K floppy
       SLOTS:            1 - trapdoor type expansion
			 1 - Zorro II slot on side
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 Parallel
			 Serial
			 15Khz RGB video
			 External Floppy
			 Integrated Keyboard
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks
			 Black & white composite Video output
 
POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - 512K FAST RAM + clock module in trapdoor
			 - Up to 8M FAST RAM
			 - Hard Drive with expansion modules
			 - 020,030,040 CPU and FPU with expansion modules
			 - Kickstart 2.04+
			 - ...

       NOTE:  ECS models had PAL and NTSC screenmodes

@Endnode


@Node A2000 "Amiga 2000"
				@{b}Amiga 2000@{ub}


Release Date:            1987 to 1989
	 CPU:            68000 at 7.14 Mhz
	 FPU:            None
Custom Chips:            Denise - 8362 Denise, REV6.3+ had 8373 SuperDenise
			 Paula
			 Fat Agnus
			 Gary
			 Buster - ZorroII Buster DIP
       Video:            OCS or ECS (4096 colors)
  Kickstarts:            1.2, 1.3 then 2.04
	RAM :            512K CHIP, 512K FAST on board
      Drives:            Internal 880K floppy
			 SCSI HD in 2000HD models
       SLOTS:            1 - Video
			 1 - CPU
			 5 - Zorro II
			 2 - 8 bit ISA
			 2 - 16 bit ISA in line with Zorro II slots
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 Parallel
			 Serial
			 15Khz RGB video
			 External Floppy
			 5-pin DIN Keyboard connector
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks
			 Black & White composite video output

POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - 1M CHIP RAM
			 - Kickstart 3.1
			 - 020,030,040,060 or PowerPC-604 CPU with accelerator cards
			 - up to 128M RAM with expansion cards
			 - True color graphic cards
			 - SCSI and IDE controlers
			 - Video Toaster & other video manipulation hardware
			 - CDROM & other devices
			 - ...

       NOTE:  ECS models had PAL and NTSC screenmodes.
	      A few models were distributed with 68020 or 68030+FPU.


@Endnode



@Node A3000 "Amiga 3000"
				@{b}Amiga 3000 Desktop@{ub}


Release Date:            1990
	 CPU:            68030 at 16 or 25 Mhz
	 FPU:            68881-16Mhz or 68882-25Mhz
Custom Chips:            Denise - 8373 SuperDenise
			 Paula
			 Agnus  - 8372B Agnus for 2 meg CHIP RAM
			 Fat Gary
			 Amber  - De-interlacing chip to provide 31KHz video
			 SuperBuster -07, -09 and -11
			 SuperDMAC -02, -04
			 Ramsey  -04 and -07
       Video:            ECS (4096 colors)
  Kickstarts:            1.3 then 2.04
	RAM :            1M or 2M CHIP on board, up to 16M FAST (Zip) on board
      Drives:            Internal 880K floppy
			 SCSI-2 Hard drive
       SLOTS:            1 - Video
			 1 - CPU
			 4 - Zorro III
			 2 - 16 bit ISA in line with Zorro III slots
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 Parallel
			 Serial
			 15Khz RGB video
			 31Khz RGB video (Flicker fixer)
			 External Floppy
			 External SCSI-2 Connector
			 5-pin DIN Keyboard connector
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks
			 Black & White composite video output

POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - 040,060 or PowerPC-604 CPU with accelerator cards
			 - Kickstart 3.1
			 - up to 128M RAM with expansion cards
			 - True color graphic cards
			 - IDE controlers
			 - Video Toaster & other video manipulation hardware
			 - CDROM & other devices
			 - ...


@Endnode


@Node A3000T "Amiga 3000 Tower"
				@{b}Amiga 3000 Tower@{ub}


Release Date:            1991
	 CPU:            68030 at 25 Mhz
	 FPU:            68882 at 25Mhz
Custom Chips:            Denise - 8373 SuperDenise
			 Paula
			 Agnus  - 8372B Agnus for 2 meg CHIP RAM
			 Fat Gary
			 Amber  - De-interlacing chip to provide 31KHz video
			 SuperBuster -07, -09 and -11
			 SuperDMAC -02, -04
			 Ramsey -04 and -07
       Video:            ECS (4096 colors)
  Kickstarts:            2.04
	RAM :            2M CHIP, 4M FAST on board, up to 16M FAST (Zip)
      Drives:            Internal 880K floppy
			 SCSI-2 Hard drive
       SLOTS:            1 - Video
			 1 - CPU
			 5 - Zorro III
			 2 - 16 bit ISA
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 Parallel
			 Serial
			 15Khz RGB video
			 31Khz RGB video (Flicker fixer)
			 External Floppy
			 External SCSI-2 Connector
			 5-pin DIN Keyboard connector
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks
			 Black & White composite video output

POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - 040,060 or PowerPC-604 CPU with accelerator cards
			 - Kickstart 3.1
			 - up to 128M RAM with expansion cards
			 - True color graphic cards
			 - IDE controlers
			 - Video Toaster & other video manipulation hardware
			 - CDROM & other devices
			 - ...

       NOTE:  PC Speaker on the casing.

@EndNode


@Node CDTV "CDTV"
			    @{b}CDTV@{ub}


Release Date:            1991
	 CPU:            68000 at 7.14 Mhz
	 FPU:            None
Custom Chips:            Denise - 8373 SuperDenise
			 Paula
			 Agnus
			 Gary
       Video:            ECS (4096 colors)
  Kickstarts:            1.3 then 2.05
	RAM :            1M Chip on board
      Drives:            Internal Single speed CDROM
       SLOTS:            1 - Credit card type (to save games scores)
			 1 - Video
			 1 - DMA extension
       PORTS:            Mouse & Infrared Joystick
			 Parallel
			 Serial
			 15Khz RGB video
			 External Floppy
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks (16 bit)
			 Color composite Video output
			 MIDI In/Out
			 Headphone Jack

POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - up to 8M fast RAM
			 - Keyboard
			 - Floppy drive
			 - Hard Drive
			 - ...

       NOTE:  This machine was easy to turn into an A500 clone with a few add-ons.

@Endnode


@Node A600 "Amiga 600"
			      @{b}Amiga 600@{ub}


Release Date:            1991
	 CPU:            68000 at 7.14 Mhz
	 FPU:            None
Custom Chips:            Denise - 8373 SuperDenise
			 Paula
			 Agnus
			 Gayle
       Video:            ECS (4096 colors)
  Kickstarts:            1.2 then 1.3
	RAM :            1M Chip on board
      Drives:            Internal 880K floppy
			 2.5" IDE HD on selected models
       SLOTS:            1 - PCMCIA type II
			 1 - trapdoor type expansion
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 Parallel
			 Serial
			 15Khz RGB video
			 External Floppy
			 Integrated Keyboard
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks
			 Color composite Video output


POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - up to 8M RAM
			 - PCMCIA SCSI Adaptor
			 - CDROM & other devices
			 - ...

       NOTE:  There was no numeric keypad on the A600.


@Endnode


@Node A1200 "Amiga 1200"
				@{b}Amiga 1200@{ub}

Release Date:            1992 (CBM) and 1995 (AT)
	 CPU:            68020 at 14.28 Mhz
	 FPU:            None
Custom Chips:            Lisa
			 Alice
			 Paula
			 Gayle
			 Budgie
       Video:            AGA (16.8M colors)
  Kickstarts:            3.0 or 3.1
	RAM :            2M Chip on board
      Drives:            Internal 880K or 1.76M (rare) floppy
			 2.5" IDE HD on selected models
       SLOTS:            1 - Trapdoor type expansion
			 1 - PCMCIA type II
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 Parallel
			 Serial
			 15Khz-31Khz RGB video
			 External Floppy
			 Integrated Keyboard
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks
			 Color composite Video output

POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - 030,040,060 or PowerPC-603 or 604 CPU with accelerator cards
			 - up to 128M RAM with expansion cards
			 - PCMCIA SCSI Controler
			 - CDROM & other devices

			 With tower kit:
			 - Zorro II-III slots adaptor
			 - True color graphic cards
			 - SCSI and IDE controlers

			 - ...

	NOTE:  With a tower kit, the 1200 can be as upgradable as a 4000.

@Endnode


@Node A4000 "Amiga 4000 Desktop"

			   @{b}Amiga 4000 Desktop@{ub}


Release Date:            1992-1993
	 CPU:            68030 at 25Mhz or 68040 at 25Mhz
	 FPU:            none or 68040 built-in FPU
Custom Chips:            Lisa
			 Alice
			 Paula
			 Bridgette
			 Buster - Superbuster -09 or -11
			 Ramsey - Ramsey -07
       Video:            AGA (16.8M colors)
  Kickstarts:            3.0
	RAM :            2M CHIP + 2M or 4M FAST, up to 16M FAST (SIMM) on board
      Drives:            Internal 1.76M floppy
			 3.5" IDE Hard drive
       SLOTS:            1 - Video
			 1 - CPU
			 4 - Zorro III
			 3 - 16 bit ISA in line with Zorro III slots
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 Parallel
			 Serial
			 15-31Khz RGB video
			 External Floppy
			 PS/2 type Keyboard connector
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks

POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - 040,060 or PowerPC-604 CPU with accelerator cards
			 - Kickstart 3.1
			 - up to 128M RAM with expansion cards
			 - True color graphic cards
			 - SCSI and IDE controlers
			 - Video Toaster 4000 & other video manipulation hardware
			 - CDROM & other devices
			 - ...

@Endnode


@Node A4000T "Amiga 4000 Tower"

			    @{b}Amiga 4000 Tower@{ub}

Release Date:            1993 (CBM) and 1995 (AT)
	 CPU:            68040 or LC040 at 25Mhz
	 FPU:            68040 built-in FPU
Custom Chips:            Lisa
			 Alice
			 Paula
			 Bridgette
			 Superbuster -11
			 Ramsey -07
       Video:            AGA (16.8M colors)
  Kickstarts:            3.0 or 3.1
	RAM :            2M CHIP + 4M FAST, up to 16M FAST (SIMM) on board
      Drives:            Internal 1.76M floppy
			 3.5" IDE HD or SCSI-2
       SLOTS:            2 - Video
			 1 - CPU
			 5 - Zorro III
			 3 - 16 bit ISA in line with Zorro III slots
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 Parallel
			 Serial
			 15-31Khz RGB video
			 External SCSI connector
			 External Floppy
			 PS/2 type Keyboard connector
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks

POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - 040,060 or PowerPC-604 CPU with accelerator cards
			 - up to 128M RAM with expansion cards
			 - True color graphic cards
			 - SCSI and IDE controlers
			 - Video Toaster 4000 & other video manipulation hardware
			 - CDROM & other devices
			 - ...

@Endnode


@Node CD32 "CD32"
				@{b}CD32@{ub}


Release Date:            1993
	 CPU:            68EC020 at 14.28 Mhz
	 FPU:            None
Custom Chips:            Lisa
			 Alice
			 Paula
			 Akiko
       Video:            AGA (16.8M colors)
  Kickstarts:            3.1
	RAM :            2M Chip on board, 1k flash ram (To save games scores)
      Drives:            Double-speed internal CDROM
       SLOTS:            1 - Expansion
       PORTS:            Mouse & Joystick
			 S-Video output
			 15Khz-31Khz RGB video
			 Stereo RCA Audio jacks (16 bit)
			 Headphone jack
			 Color composite Video output

POSSIBLE EXPANSIONS:     - 68030 CPU+FPU with SX-32 expansion module
			 - MPEG movies module

			 With SX-1 or SX-32 modules:
			 - Up to 128M RAM (SIMM)
			 - 3.5" IDE HD
			 - 880K or 1.76M External Floppy
			 - PC/AT Keyboard

			 - ...

       NOTE:  With the expansion modules, the CD32 can turn into a complete computer.

@Endnode


